First substitute \(x=-i\) into \(f(x)=\frac{x+1}{x-4}\):

\[
f(-i)=\frac{-i+1}{-i-4}=\frac{1 - i}{-4 - i}.
\]

Now multiply top and bottom by the conjugate of the denominator, \(-4+i\):

\[
\frac{1 - i}{-4 - i}\cdot\frac{-4 + i}{-4 + i}
=\frac{(1 - i)(-4 + i)}{(-4 - i)(-4 + i)}
=\frac{-4 + i +4i -i^2}{(-4)^2 - (i)^2}
=\frac{-4 +5i -(-1)}{16 -(-1)}
=\frac{-3 +5i}{17}.
\]

Hence

\[
\boxed{f(-i)=\frac{-3+5i}{17}=\,-\frac{3}{17}+\frac{5}{17}i.}
\]
